      <h2>What Does This SEO Audit Check?</h2>
      <p>This comprehensive audit evaluates your website across <strong>11 categories</strong> with over <strong>55 individual checks</strong>. Each check is scored and weighted by impact, giving you an overall SEO Health Score from 0 to 100.</p>

      <p><strong>Technical SEO (25%)</strong> checks your HTTPS setup, robots.txt, XML sitemap, mobile viewport, canonical tags, redirect chains, mixed content, soft 404s, and hreflang tags. These are foundational signals that tell search engines whether they can crawl and index your site properly.</p>

      <p><strong>On-Page SEO (20%)</strong> evaluates your title tags, meta descriptions, H1 structure, heading hierarchy, internal links, Open Graph tags, and Twitter Cards. These elements directly influence how your pages appear in search results and how users interact with them.</p>

      <p><strong>Content Quality (22%)</strong> analyzes word count, readability, placeholder text detection, blog presence, content duplication, and passage structure for AI extractability. Content is the #1 ranking factor — thin pages with under 300 words rarely rank for competitive terms.</p>

      <p><strong>Performance (15%)</strong> uses the Google PageSpeed Insights API to measure your real Core Web Vitals: Largest Contentful Paint (LCP, threshold: 2.0s), Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS), Interaction to Next Paint (INP), Time to First Byte (TTFB), and overall Performance Score. Speed directly impacts rankings and user experience.</p>

      <p><strong>Authority & Backlinks (10%)</strong> pulls live data from a professional SEO database to show your Domain Rating (0-100), total backlinks, referring domains, referring IPs, broken backlinks, total ranking keywords, position distribution, and estimated monthly organic traffic. This is the same caliber of data enterprise SEO platforms use. Most free audit tools skip authority entirely.</p>

      <p><strong>Schema Markup (12%)</strong> checks for JSON-LD structured data, LocalBusiness or Organization schema, BreadcrumbList, WebSite with SearchAction, Person/Author, VideoObject, and FAQ schema. Schema helps Google understand your business and enables rich snippets in search results.</p>

      <p><strong>AI Search Readiness (5%)</strong> evaluates whether your content is structured for AI-powered search engines like ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews. FAQ sections, Q&A patterns, and indexability all factor in.</p>

      <p><strong>GEO / AIO (5%)</strong> checks llms.txt compliance, passage structure scoring (150-300 word chunks), direct answer formatting, question-based headings, and content freshness per-platform. AI search is the fastest-growing channel — optimize for it now.</p>

      <p><strong>Images (5%)</strong> checks alt text coverage and image optimization signals. Images without alt text hurt accessibility and SEO, while unoptimized images slow down your pages.</p>

      <p><strong>Analytics (5%)</strong> detects your tracking stack — Google Analytics 4, Google Tag Manager, Meta Pixel, LinkedIn Insight, Hotjar, and Microsoft Clarity. Proper tracking is essential for measuring SEO ROI.</p>

      <p><strong>Security (5%)</strong> checks HTTPS enforcement, HSTS, Content Security Policy, X-Frame-Options, and X-Content-Type-Options headers. Security is a ranking signal and builds user trust.</p>

      <h2>How the Scoring Works</h2>
      <p>Your overall score is a weighted average across all 11 categories. Technical SEO and On-Page SEO carry the most weight because they are the foundational signals Google evaluates first. Performance and Content Quality are next, followed by the new Authority & Backlinks category, Schema Markup, AI Readiness, GEO/AIO, Images, Analytics, and Security.</p>
      <p><strong>A (90-100):</strong> Your site has excellent SEO fundamentals. Focus on content velocity and review generation. <strong>B (75-89):</strong> Good foundation with specific areas to improve. Check the Top Priorities. <strong>C (60-74):</strong> Several important checks are failing and likely costing you rankings. <strong>D (40-59):</strong> Multiple fundamental issues need attention. <strong>F (below 40):</strong> Critical problems that may be making your site invisible in search.</p>

